               <p>JOHN SYMONS HIGGS. I live on the Pavement, Moorfields. On the 2nd of September I was in <placeName id="t18300916-179-crimeloc924">Long-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-179-crimeloc924" type="placeName" value="Long-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-179-crimeloc924" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-179-off922 t18300916-179-crimeloc924"></join>; I felt a hand at my pocket; I turned and missed my handkerchief; two little boys pointed to the prisoner; he was then about three yards from me; he crossed the street between two carts; I crossed, collared him, and told him he had my handkerchief; he denied it; I searched him, but could not find it - I then desired him to take up his apron, and in his waistband I found this handkerchief.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I picked it up.</p>
               <p>THOMAS BARKER. I took the prisoner in charge.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>The prisoner received a good character.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 15.</p>
